# RPG integrations

## Separation of concerns

| Layer | Plugin | RPG plugin may |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| Skill XP & levels | AuraSkills | Listen events, grant XP via API, apply StatModifiers |
| Towns & regions | Civs | Listen events, read managers, use `%civs_*%` |
| Money | Vault | deposit/withdraw, balance checks |
| Unlocks | LuckPerms | grant nodes/tracks on quest/perk completion |
| Display | PAPI | Register `%rpg_*%`; consume `%civs_*%` / `%auraskills_*%` |

## Do NOT duplicate AuraSkills XP

- No parallel skill level storage, XP tables, or level-up logic in RPG plugin.
- Quest rewards: `user.addSkillXp(Skill, amount)` or temporary multiplier on `XpGainEvent.setAmount()`.
- Perk bonuses: `StatModifier` with id `rpg_<perk_id>` — remove on perk revoke.
- Wait for `SkillsLoadEvent` before any AuraSkills API access.

## Civs integration

- Prefer **Bukkit events** over direct manager calls for quest triggers.
- Safe events: `RegionCreatedEvent`, `TownCreatedEvent`, `TownEvolveEvent`, `EnterCombatEvent`, `PlayerAcceptsTownInviteEvent`.
- Avoid: `GainExpEvent`, `SpellPreCastEvent` (not fired in Civs 1.11.6).
- Civs mana (`%civs_mana%`) and AuraSkills mana are separate — document which a perk uses.

## Hooks must degrade gracefully

When `config.yml` sets `integrations.<plugin>.enabled: false` or plugin absent, hook no-ops without errors.

## plugin.yml load order

```yaml
depend: [Vault]
softdepend: [Civs, AuraSkills, PlaceholderAPI, LuckPerms]
loadafter: [Vault, Civs, AuraSkills, PlaceholderAPI, LuckPerms]
```
